name: Oven Baked Sweet Potato Fries
author: United Soybean Board
summary: Need a side dish? Bake a batch of sweet potato fries that will please your friends and family. Soybean oil, labeled vegetable oil, helps brown evenly. Season as you please!
ingredients: 2 large sweet potatoes, peeled, cut into 1x3-inch wedges
½ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
directions: Position rack in upper third of oven and preheat oven to 425 degrees F
Spray baking sheet with non-stick spray
Place sweet potatoes and soybean oil in large bowl, toss lightly
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika
Arrange potatoes in a single layer on prepared baking sheet, being sure not to overcrowd
Bake until tender and golden brown, turning occasionally
